      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind bake the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}} and {{icing-sugar}} until the mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add the {{eggs}} (pastry yolk) and 1 to 2 tbsp cold water and press to a smooth dough. Wrap and chill for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll to 3 mm thick and line a 23 cm deep tart tin. Blind bake with paper and beans for 15 minutes, remove beans and paper, and bake for 5 more minutes. Reduce the oven to 160°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the custard and bake, 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm the {{double-cream}}, {{whole-milk}}, and {{caster-sugar}} gently in a saucepan until the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat. Whisk the whole {{eggs}} and {{eggs}} (yolks) with the {{vanilla-extract}} in a bowl, then pour the warm cream mixture over while whisking. Strain through a sieve into a jug.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the custard into the warm pastry case. Grate {{nutmeg-whole}} generously over the surface. Bake at 160°C fan for 30 to 35 minutes, until the edges are set and the centre trembles. Cool in the tin for 1 hour before releasing. Serve at room temperature or cold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
